               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;The end of &lt;b&gt;b3&lt;/b&gt; is restored to &lt;i&gt;śäk kälyme(ntwaṃ)&lt;/i&gt; in [[Carling, DThTA]]: 204 - translation follows Carling! (TI)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the middle of &lt;b&gt;b4&lt;/b&gt;, [[Carling, DThTA]]: 204 reads &lt;i&gt;koṃ-[ypānt kä]lymentwaṃ&lt;/i&gt; – translation follows Carling! [[Peyrot 2011]]: 44 reads &lt;i&gt;koṃ-wmānt&lt;/i&gt;. BTW translit has &lt;i&gt;koṃ nṣān_t\&lt;/i&gt;? (TI)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to [[TochSprR(A)]]:210, the meter is 20|22|10|15. (BK)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;i&gt;cmalune&lt;/i&gt; should be preceded by a subcola of 4 syllables, but &lt;i&gt; – – lpāt&lt;/i&gt; is too short. (BK)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3&lt;/b&gt;: I would suggest restoring &lt;i&gt;kälyme(yntu)&lt;/i&gt; instead of &lt;i&gt;kälyme(yäntu)&lt;/i&gt;. Otherwise the line doesn't scan. (BK)&lt;/p&gt;</item>
