         <div type="project_comment">
            <p>&lt;project_comment&gt;&lt;p&gt;The end of &lt;ref type="ms" target="__b3"/&gt; is restored to &lt;hi&gt;śäk kälyme(ntwaṃ)&lt;/hi&gt; in &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;204&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; - translation follows Carling! (TI)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the middle of &lt;ref type="ms" target="__b4"/&gt;, &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;204&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; reads &lt;hi&gt;koṃ-[ypānt kä]lymentwaṃ&lt;/hi&gt; – translation follows Carling! &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:peyrot2011"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;44&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; reads &lt;hi&gt;koṃ-wmānt&lt;/hi&gt;. BTW translit has &lt;hi&gt;koṃ nṣān_t\&lt;/hi&gt;? (TI)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1921"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;210&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt;, the meter is 20|22|10|15. (BK)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;ref type="ms" target="__b2"/&gt;:&lt;hi&gt;cmalune&lt;/hi&gt; should be preceded by a subcola of 4 syllables, but &lt;hi&gt; – – lpāt&lt;/hi&gt; is too short. (BK)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;ref type="ms" target="__b3"/&gt;: I would suggest restoring &lt;hi&gt;kälyme(yntu)&lt;/hi&gt; instead of &lt;hi&gt;kälyme(yäntu)&lt;/hi&gt;. Otherwise the line doesn't scan. (BK)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/project_comment&gt;</p>
